    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>THE CLINTON PRINCIPLE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Leter by David A Sutter on Garry Wills' Jan 19 article on beliefs of Pres Clinton (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In ''The Clinton Principle'' (Jan. 19), Garry Wills implies that Clinton as President is making it up as he goes. But improvisation is the nature and strength of a democratic society. The initial architects of our nation -- Washington, Jefferson, Adams -- improvised from day to day, year to year, to keep our ship of state afloat.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>In ''The Clinton Principle'' (Jan. 19), Garry Wills implies that Clinton as President is making it up as he goes. But improvisation is the nature and strength of a democratic society. The initial architects of our nation -- Washington, Jefferson, Adams -- improvised from day to day, year to year, to keep our ship of state afloat.</p>
        <p>To quote Shakespeare, ''We are but warriors for the working-day.''</p>
        <p>DAVID A. SUTTER  San Francisco</p>
      </block>
